     <elementSpec ident="foreign" mode="change">
      <exemplum>
       <p>The Latin phrase "Ab urbe condita" is not in the same language (Portuguese) as the rest of
        the paragraph </p>
       <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
        <p>E calcando a espada debaixo do pé esquerdo, curvou-a: <foreign>Ab urbe condita</foreign>,
         da fundação de Roma, no ano seiscentos e três. </p></egXML>
      </exemplum>
      <exemplum>
       <!-- POR0031-->
       <p>In this example, the whole quotation is given in a different language (Spanish). The
        foreign language concerned is specified by means of the <att>xml:lang</att> attribute. The
         <gi>foreign</gi> element can only be used to enclose words and phrases directly, rather
        than to enclose <gi>l</gi> or <gi>quote</gi> elements, and must therefore be repeated for
        the content of each line. </p>
       <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
        <p>E cá fóra veriamos o velho mendigo no mesmo lugar ainda, cantando ao som da sanfona:</p>
        <quote>
         <l><foreign xml:lang="es">«Rosa fresca, rosa fresca,</foreign></l>
         <l><foreign xml:lang="es">tan garrida y con amor;</foreign></l>
         <l><foreign xml:lang="es">quando vos tuve em mis braços,</foreign></l>
         <l><foreign xml:lang="es">no vos supe servir, no,</foreign></l>
         <l><foreign xml:lang="es">y agora que os serviria</foreign></l>
         <l><foreign xml:lang="es">no vos puedo aver no.</foreign>
          <ref target="#note2"/>
         </l>
        </quote></egXML>
      </exemplum>
      <exemplum>
       <p>An alternative and more economical encoding for the foregoing example: </p>
       <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
        <p>E cá fóra veriamos o velho mendigo no mesmo lugar ainda, cantando ao som da sanfona:</p>
        <quote xml:lang="es">
         <l>«Rosa fresca, rosa fresca,</l>
         <l>tan garrida y con amor;</l>
         <!-- ... etc. -->
        </quote></egXML>
      </exemplum>
